   "body" : "I am proposing a step by step guide to install WSL on a non-system drive.\r\nWhile installing the wsl as advised in the build-windows.md doc, we could not be able to build bitcoin due to a lack of space in the C:\\ drive.\r\nThat would also make impossible to run tests (units, regression and functional).\r\n\r\nBut, if the install is done on a non-system drive (D:\\, F:\\...), the user would have more spaces and possibilities to install a linux distro, compile bitcoin and run tests.\r\n\r\nThis guide is here to help with detailed steps and it worked for me.",
